Basics

Gradle scripts are configuration scripts, as the scripts execute it configures an
specific type object.

    - For example: As a build script executes, it configures an object of type Project
    - This object is called the delegate object of script

Type of scrips : Delegate object
Build Script    - Project
Init Script     - Gradle
Settings Script - Settings

Each gradle script implements the Script interface

    - it defines properties and methods which we can use in the scripts


Core Type: Central types which in Gradle Scripts

Project: T
he main API interface thatwe can use to interact with Gradle from build file. From a Project
we have programmatic access to all of Gradle's features


Task:
It represents a single atomic piece of work for a build, such as compiling classes or generating
javadoc

Gradle, Settings, ... so on

Container Types: Its handle various declarative elements (dependencies, configurations
, artifacts, tasks)

TaskContainer: it is responsible for managing a set of Task instances.

ConfigurationContainer: It is responsible for declaring and managing configurations


